## 3. Current baseline and evolution

What exists today, what is exploratory, and where plans live. Update as features ship; durable principles (§2) should not need rewrites each release unless **values** change.

### Compiler and build pipeline

- **Author-facing output** is **HTML-oriented** (sites and documents). **Internal** representation—strings, IR, DOM walks, structured emitters—is an **implementation detail** and will evolve ([_reference/refactors/compilation/compilation-review.md](_reference/refactors/compilation/compilation-review.md), [_reference/refactors/compilation/compilation-plan.md](_reference/refactors/compilation/compilation-plan.md), [_reference/plans/_archive/compilation-refactor.md](_reference/plans/_archive/compilation-refactor.md)).
- **Incremental builds** at the Aero level (dependency-aware dirty sets, persistent caches) are **direction**, not fully realized yet: [_reference/refactors/incremental/incremental-builds.md](_reference/refactors/incremental/incremental-builds.md).

### Type system and author-time guarantees

- **Today:** Partial type safety in build scripts, content collections, language-server tooling, and some template/build-time workflows; route manifests, params, component props across template boundaries, route context, and loader outputs are not yet modeled end to end.
- **Direction:** Move toward full compile-time coverage via generated route types, stronger prop typing, typed loader/context proposals, and unified diagnostics. [_reference/exploration/type-system/index.md](_reference/exploration/type-system/index.md).

### Client interactivity and Aero-native behavior

- **Today:** Most client behavior is **delegated** to the **browser**, **HTMX**, **Alpine.js**, **vanilla JS**, or **Web Components** where appropriate. **Aero does not own the DOM** after delivery in the default mental model ([overview.md](docs/drafts/overview.md)).
- **Exploratory / planned:** Opt-in **hypermedia**, **islands**, **hydration**, and **Aero-native** navigation or reactivity are **not** forbidden by principles; they are **not** production commitments until shipped. [_reference/exploration/hypermedia-reactivity/aero-hypermedia-reactivity-overview.md](_reference/exploration/hypermedia-reactivity/aero-hypermedia-reactivity-overview.md).

### Optional builtins and async

- **Optional** first-party primitives (e.g. `<aero-async>` and related ideas) may ship in **phases** as **additions** that extend HTML—they are **not** a requirement to drop HTMX or Alpine. [_reference/exploration/async/async-support-plan.md](_reference/exploration/async/async-support-plan.md), [_reference/exploration/builtins/aero-builtins-exporation.md](_reference/exploration/builtins/aero-builtins-exporation.md).

### Standalone template runtime

- Compiled templates and `@aero-js/core` **runtime** are intended to be usable **outside** a full Vite-first app (standalone render path, ESM-first). [_reference/exploration/runtime/stanalone-runtime.md](_reference/exploration/runtime/stanalone-runtime.md), [monorepo.md](docs/drafts/monorepo.md).

### Nitro configuration

- **Nitro** integration is moving toward a single **user-owned** `nitro.config.ts` merged with Aero **invariants** in generated config; dev/build/preview parity is an active concern. [_reference/refactors/nitro/nitro-features.md](_reference/refactors/nitro/nitro-features.md).

