## 5. Framework engineering principles

Day-to-day code and architecture follow **[.agents/rules/aero-coding-principles.mdc](.agents/rules/aero-coding-principles.mdc)**—twelve principles and **priority order** when they conflict: correctness → clarity → simplicity → safety → performance → generality.

**Compiler and plugin work:** Prefer **clear boundaries** between parse, analysis, codegen, and Vite integration; **validate at boundaries** and use typed structures inside; **surface errors early** (diagnostics, compile-time checks). Large refactors should **reduce duplicated pipelines** and **unsafe string assembly** in favor of single ownership and testable units—[_reference/refactors/compilation/compilation-review.md](_reference/refactors/compilation/compilation-review.md).

